Get Games List
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

`GamesDB GetGamesList API
Call <http://wiki.thegamesdb.net/index.php?title=GetGamesList>`__

Retrieve the id, title, release date (when available) and platform for a
list of games, based off of the name, and optionally the platform and
genre. This call will always return a list of Games.

Note that GetGamesList will treat name arguments with spaces as an AND
search operation. For example searching where name="mega man" will
return all games containing both "mega" and "man" in their title. This
is different that GetGame, which would treat the same search as an OR
operation.

Get Games List by Name
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

.. code:: python

    mega_man_games = gamesdb_api.get_games_list(name="mega man")
    for game in mega_man_games:
        print game.title
        print game.platform
        print game.release_date
        print "---------------------"

**Output:**

::

