Get Games List by Name and Genre
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

Note that you can pass in genre and platform independently, name is the
only required field.

.. code:: python

    mega_man_games = gamesdb_api.get_games_list(name="mega man", platform='Sony Playstation', genre='platform')
    for game in mega_man_games:
        print game.title
        print game.platform
        print game.release_date
        print "---------------------"

**Output:**

::

    Mega Man X6
    Sony Playstation
    12/04/2001
    ---------------------
    Mega Man Legends 2
    Sony Playstation
    10/24/2000
    ---------------------
    Pac-Man World 20th Aniversary
    Sony Playstation
    09/30/1999
    ---------------------

Classes
=======

At present, there are two main class types uses to present results. The
specific entries that are populated will vary based off othe query and
the actualy data available for your object(s).

-  Game
-  id
-  title
-  release\_date
-  platform
-  overview
-  esrb\_rating
-  genres
-  players
-  coop
-  youtube\_url
-  publisher
-  developer
-  rating
-  logo\_url
-  Platform
-  id
-  name
-  alias
-  console
-  controller
-  overview
-  developer
-  manufacturer
-  cpu
-  memory
-  graphics
-  sound
-  display
-  media
-  max\_controllers
-  rating

